Media publishers from various institutions have come together in Johannesburg to discuss the trends that have affected the sector in the past few years. The Digital Media Africa conference which was first held in 2016 has brought together a number of industry leaders. In partnership with WAN-IFRA the conference is back in South Africa for the second time. The conference seeks to close the gap on the growing trends within the Digital media industry. The gathering is an effort to discuss the changing digital landscape â€“ and how it affects thousands of users not only in South Africa but the world at large. Hot on the agenda is how African publishers can explore new digital revenue models for sustainability of the business. Watch Video Below:  